<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNSUNG LIBRARIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Recently I had a phone call from the Hollywood Library. I spoke with the head 
librarian, Noreen Shaw. It seems I had inadvertently left a check in one of the 
books I had returned and Mrs. Shaw was kind enough to call and tell me.It was 
not my first meeting with Mrs. Shaw. She had been good enough to allow me a 
late return on a book I had mislaid after the earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 When I came for my check, Mrs. Shaw revealed she was relieved to find it 
wasn't someone who had come to threaten her. I was surprised to discover this 
is a frequent occurrence in the lives of our librarians. However, this did not 
seem to faze Mrs. Shaw in the least. 
</P>
<P>
 I write this letter to salute Mrs. Shaw. She is an unsung hero in a city that 
can use all the heroes it can get. I salute her hard work, her good humor, her 
dedication and simple acts of human kindness. I'm sure there are other Mrs. 
Shaws worthy of similar praise.  
</P>
<P>
 THOMAS LEE TULLY 
</P>
<P>
 Hollywood 
</P>
