<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: THE WORKPLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Violence Invades Workplace, Study Finds: One of every six violent crimes occur 
at work, affecting nearly a million victims nationwide each year, according to 
a Justice Department report. The Bureau of Justice Statistics found that 16% of 
all assaults, 8% of all rapes and 7% of all robberies take place at work. The 
study said victims lose an estimated 1.8 million workdays each year and $55 
million in wages because of the crimes. 
</P>
