<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BOXING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wangila Napunyi, a 1988 Olympic boxing gold medalist from Kenya, remained in 
critical condition in Las Vegas with a head injury suffered during a fight. 
</P>
<P>
 Napunyi was fighting David Gonzales of Houston in a scheduled 10-round 
welterweight match Friday night at the Aladdin Hotel when the referee stopped 
the bout, won by Gonzales. Napunyi later collapsed in his dressing room. 
</P>
<P>
 Albert Capanna, who performed surgery on Napunyi at University Medical Center, 
said "He is not getting any better. . . . It doesn't look really good. That 
doesn't mean it can't get better." 
</P>
</TEXT>
