<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHILLIPS TO DEFEND TITLE AT FORUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Champion Verno Phillips and No. 1 contender Jaime Llanes will meet tonight at 
the Forum in a World Boxing Organization junior-middleweight title bout. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers decided to return to holding fights on Monday nights, abandoning a 
short-lived experiment with Fridays. 
</P>
<P>
 It is the second consecutive Los Angeles-based championship fight for the 
lightly regarded WBO, which sanctioned a junior-welterweight match at the Grand 
Olympic Auditorium on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The New York-based Phillips (22-4-1, 12 knockouts) won the WBO championship, 
which is not considered a major title, in Phoenix on Oct. 30 over local 
favorite Lupe Aquino, and is undefeated (14-0-1) in his last 15 bouts. This is 
Phillips' first official defense. 
</P>
<P>
 Llanes is 27-2, with 26 KOs, and has won 24 consecutive bouts. 
</P>
<P>
 Also on the card is a scheduled 10-rounder between the World Boxing Assn.'s 
No. 2-ranked lightweight, Fabian Tejada (37-3-2, 29 KOs), and Mauricio Aceves, 
who has lost his last six fights. TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</TEXT>
