<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; SUSPECT IN FATAL SHOOTING ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police on Sunday arrested a Ventura man who investigators suspect shot and 
killed a 23-year-old transient in a Ventura home last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas A. Corral was taken into custody in Las Vegas by Ventura police, but 
further details on the arrest were not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
 Corral is suspected of storming into his girlfriend's Ventura home last 
Thursday and killing Roger Rowland, whom police described as a drifter, with a 
single gunshot to the stomach. He died about 45 minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
 A police spokeswoman said Sunday the warrant for Corral's arrest was issued 
sometime over the weekend by a Ventura County judge. Authorities said Corral 
was also wanted by police in connection with a 1991 kidnaping. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are also seeking Ruben Viveros, 19, for questioning. Viveros allegedly 
accompanied Corral into the apartment on Kirk Avenue where the shooting 
occurred. 
</P>
<P>
 As of late Sunday, Viveros had not been located by authorities. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said Corral's 18-year-old girlfriend, who is also the mother of 
his infant, lives in the apartment. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Corral has been a fugitive since being identified as a suspect in 
the 1991 ransom kidnaping of a 3-year-old Los Angeles boy. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
