<P>
SANTA ANA TO CUT SOME WALK-IN SERVICES AT CITY HALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Hall will curtail some walk-in services by an hour a day beginning next 
Monday, offering them from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday through Friday, instead of 8 
a.m. to 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Activities to be affected include cashier services for payment of municipal 
utility bills, parking citations and dog licenses, and the taking of business 
license applications. All other City Hall services will continue to be offered 
from 8 a.m. through 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 City staff members will continue to answer the phones beginning at 8 a.m. 
</P>
